05433nam a22007215i 9782759829088DE-B159720230529101353.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||230529t20232023fr     fo  d z      eng d  a97827598290887 a10.1051/978-2-7598-2908-82doi  a(DE-B1597)650568  a(OCoLC)1371108344  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  afrcFR 7aMED0030702bisacsh0482pa617.5qDE-10100aV-Shape Bichannel Spinal Endoscopy: Technique and Practice /ced. by Shisheng HE. 1aLes Ulis : bEDP Sciences, c[2023] 4c©2023  a1 online resource (174 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tContributors -- tPreface -- tIntroduction -- tContents -- tList of Abbreviations -- tChapter 1 Brief History of Spinal Endoscopic Surgery -- tChapter 2 Principles of V-Shape Bichannel Endoscopy System Design -- tChapter 3 Clinical Applied Anatomy for V-Shape Bichannel Endoscopy -- tChapter 4 V-Shape Bichannel Endoscopy Assisted Discectomy and Decompression -- tChapter 5 V-Shape Bichannel Endoscopic Lumbar Fusion -- tChapter 6 Clinical Application of V-Shape Bichannel Endoscopy -- tChapter 7 Lumbar Surgery Rehabilitation0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aTechnology related to spinal endoscopy has undergone rapid development over the past 30 years. Some surgical techniques, such as the Unilateral Biportal Endoscopy (UBE), have been widely applied. Meanwhile, the surgical instruments of spinal endoscopy have also significantly evolved. However, there are still problems in dealing with complex spinal disorders and diseases, including limited surgical space, high rate of equipment damage and low surgical efficiency. In this context, Professor Shisheng He and his team at the Tenth People’s Hospital of Tongji University developed the V-shape Bichannel Endoscopy System (VBE). As a brand new uniportal bichannel endoscope unlike other existing endoscopes in clinical application, the VBE allows safe and efficient transforaminal lumbar decompression and interbody fusion to be performed under real-time and full-time endoscopic monitoring. The VBE integrates the working channel and endoscopic channel so that the two become one in a “V” shape. It requires only one incision. Both positions of the instruments and the endoscope are fixed, which makes it easy to identify the surgical site during operation. It is a completely different type of endoscope to the UBE and represents a new surgical concept. The VBE is also the first endoscopic system that can be performed in both air and water medium. As a result, the surgical procedure is more convenient and easier for surgeons to master. This book is edited by Professor Shisheng HE with contributions of more than 25 experts in minimally invasive spine surgery. It provides detailed information on the design principles, indications, surgical approaches, and surgical techniques of the VBE. The authors hope that this book will be useful to those who are committed to spinal endoscopic surgery.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aMEDICAL / Allied Health Services / Imaging Technologies.2bisacsh1 aHE, Shisheng, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2023 Part 2z978311117804208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2023 Englishz978311131921608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2023z9783111318615oZDB-23-DPM08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEDP Sciences Fron